How to run locally (smoke test)
Ensure executable:
bash
chmod +x backend/run_prod_gunicorn.sh
Install deps:
bash
python3 -m venv backend/venv
./backend/venv/bin/pip install -r backend/requirements.txt
Run (ASGI):
bash
HOST=127.0.0.1 PORT=8000 ./backend/run_prod_gunicorn.sh
# Open http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/healthz
Production: switch systemd to ASGI
Edit service file 
backend/deploy/reporting-api-gunicorn.service
:
Set WorkingDirectory=/abs/path/to/backend
Set ExecStart=/abs/path/to/backend/run_prod_gunicorn.sh
Optionally set EnvironmentFile=/etc/reporting/reporting-api.env
Ensure RUN_SCHEDULER=0 here if you run a separate scheduler leader (only one instance should have it on).
Replace current service and reload:
bash
sudo cp backend/deploy/reporting-api-gunicorn.service /etc/systemd/system/reporting-api.service
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable reporting-api
sudo systemctl restart reporting-api
sudo systemctl status reporting-api -n 100
